: double 2 * ;
: m < 1 2 3 > ' double map ;
: outer m . cr ;
outer

clear
[ 1 2 3 ] [: 2 * :] map .
[ 5 5 7 ] [: 1 + :] map .
[ ] [: 99 :] map .
: triple 3 * ;
[ 10 20 30 ] ' triple map .

clear
[ 1 2 3 ] [ 10 20 30 ] ' + 2 mapn .
[ 1 2 3 ] [ 10 20 30 ] [ 100 200 300 ] [: + + :] 3 mapn .
[ ] [ ] ' + 2 mapn .
[ 5 ] ' negate 1 mapn .
: avg + + 3 / ;
[ 3 6 9 ] [ 4 5 6 ] [ 5 4 3 ] ' avg 3 mapn .

clear
\ keep elements greater than 3
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] [: 3 gt :] filter .

\ keep none / keep all
[ 1 2 3 ] [: 100 gt :] filter .
[ 1 2 3 ] [: 0 gt :] filter .

\ empty source
[ ] [: 0 gt :] filter .

\ filter over a set (members stay sorted)
< 5 1 3 2 4 > [: 2 gt :] filter .

\ composes with size and map
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] [: 3 gt :] filter size .
[ 1 2 3 4 ] [: 2 gt :] filter [: dup * :] map .

\ failures
[ 1 2 3 ] 5 filter
5 [: 0 gt :] filter
[ 1 2 3 ] [: dup :] filter

\ --- pfilter: parallel filter, results identical to filter ---

\ pfilter (shortcut: num-cores workers, claim 1) equals filter
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] dup [: 3 gt :] filter swap [: 3 gt :] pfilter = .
1 500 range dup [: 7 mod 0= :] filter swap [: 7 mod 0= :] pfilter = .

\ pfilter-ext (explicit worker_count and items_per_claim) equals filter
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 ] dup [: 2 mod 0= :] filter swap 4 2 [: 2 mod 0= :] pfilter-ext = .
1 500 range dup [: 7 mod 0= :] filter swap 8 1 [: 7 mod 0= :] pfilter-ext = .

\ allocating predicate (a fresh string per element) equals filter
1 200 range dup [: "{0}" format size 1 gt :] filter swap [: "{0}" format size 1 gt :] pfilter = .

\ concrete: keep evens, order preserved
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] [: 2 mod 0= :] pfilter .

\ keep none / keep all
[ 1 2 3 ] [: 0 :] pfilter .
[ 1 2 3 ] [: 1 :] pfilter .

\ empty source
[ ] [: 1 :] pfilter .

\ pfilter over a set (members stay sorted)
< 5 1 3 2 4 > [: 2 gt :] pfilter .

\ worker_count clamped to domain length; single worker
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 99 1 [: 2 mod 0= :] pfilter-ext .
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 1 1 [: 2 mod 0= :] pfilter-ext .

\ the source array is read, never mutated
[ 1 2 3 4 ] dup [: 2 mod 0= :] pfilter drop .

\ composes with size
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] [: 3 gt :] pfilter size .

\ failures
[ 1 2 3 ] 5 1 4 pfilter-ext
5 1 1 [: 0 gt :] pfilter-ext

clear
\ reduce ( arr init [: acc elt -- acc :] -- result ) — left fold in C.

\ sum
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] 0 [: + :] reduce . cr

\ product
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 1 [: * :] reduce . cr

\ single element
[ 5 ] 0 [: + :] reduce . cr

\ empty collection yields the initial value, combiner never runs
[ ] 42 [: + :] reduce . cr

\ non-commutative combiner pins the fold direction and operand order:
\ ((((100 - 1) - 2) - 3) = 94, with the accumulator as the left operand.
[ 1 2 3 ] 100 [: - :] reduce . cr
